*** mixtli patch: allowed-origins-and-s3 ***

1) Replace your utils/s3.js with the one in this archive.
   - Supports R2 (path-style = true) and AWS S3 (path-style = false)
   - Accepts credentials in S3_* or AWS_* env names
   - Fails early with clear errors if credentials are missing/incomplete

2) In server.js, replace ALLOWED_ORIGINS parsing with src-snippets/server.allowed-origins.snippet.js
   - Accepts JSON array: ["https://a.com","https://b.com"]
   - Or single string:   "https://a.com"
   - Or CSV string:      https://a.com,https://b.com
   - Defaults to ["http://localhost:5173"]

